newsitem.title: UK: IPE Brent breaks resistance, hits five month high.
newsitem.headline: IPE Brent breaks resistance, hits five month high.

text.p: IPE Brent crude oil futures hit five month highs on Tuesday because of what traders said were technical factors.
Oct Brent was trading at $22.88 per barrel at 1739 GMT, overtaking the $22.85 contract high of September 3.
"It is a technical move," one IPE dealer said, adding that a break of resistance at $22.60/$22.65 earlier had prompted the move higher.
Brokers said a key market pointer was Oct NYMEX crude futures, which broke through strong resistance at $24.00.
